text.section:
No employer shall knowingly allow, permit, or authorize a driver to drive a commercial vehicle during any period in which the driver:
Has had his commercial driver's license suspended, revoked, or canceled by any state;
Is currently disqualified from driving a commercial vehicle;
Is subject to an out-of-service order in any state;
Has more than one (1) driver's license;
Does not currently hold a valid commercial driver's license; or
Is in violation of any of the railroad crossing offenses or conduct set forth in KRS 189.500, 189.560, or 189.565.
